Package com.bindroid.trackable

Interface Summary
Tracker Provides an interface for tracking Trackables.
 

Class Summary
ComparingTrackableField<T> A TrackableField that uses an EqualityComparer to determine whether a value has changed when calling ComparingTrackableField.set(Object).
Trackable Provides an object to which Tracker can subscribe for notifications as well as methods that allow a Tracker to evaluate an Action or Function while subscribing to notifications for any trackers used during that evaluation.
TrackableBoolean Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for boolean primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
TrackableByte Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for byte primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
TrackableChar Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for char primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
TrackableCollection<T> A List implementation that implements Trackable on all of its methods, notifying Trackers whenever a change to the list occurs.
TrackableDouble Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for double primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
TrackableField<T> Implements a Trackable that stores a value.
TrackableFloat Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for float primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
TrackableInt Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for integer primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
TrackableLong Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for long primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
TrackableShort Provides a TrackableField-like implementation for short primitives, allowing you to avoid the cost of boxing and unboxing values.
